.TH SHELL_FUNCTIONS 1 "April 22, 2024" "Holberton Coding School" "Shell Commands Manual"

.SH NAME
shell_functions \- Manual for Shell Functions and Signal Handler

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shell_functions

.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
This manual documents various functions and a signal handler used in a simple shell program.

.B Signal Handler
.P
The signal handler function, \fBsigintH\fR, handles the SIGINT signal (Ctrl+C) by writing a custom prompt to standard error (\fBstderr\fR).

.B String Functions
.P
The following functions are used for string manipulation:
.TP
.B str_concat
Concatenates two strings and returns a pointer to the concatenated string.

.TP
.B _realloc
Custom memory reallocation function to resize dynamically allocated memory blocks.

.B Tokenization Functions
.P
These functions tokenize input strings based on specific delimiters:
.TP
.B hsh_tokenizer
Tokenizes input strings using a delimiter and returns an array of tokens.

.TP
.B tokenizer_path
Tokenizes input strings using a different delimiter and returns an array of tokens.

.B Input Validation Function
.P
The \fBvalidate_input\fR function validates user input arguments and checks for the existence of specified files.

.B Space Validation Function
.P
The \fBvalidate_spaces\fR function checks if a given input string contains only whitespace characters.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR signal (7),
.BR malloc (3),
.BR strtok (3)

